public static Opcode opMAILBOX_OPEN(IExpression<Data8> NO, IExpression<Data8> BOXNAME, IExpression<Data8> TYPES, IExpression<Data8> FIFOSIZE, IExpression<Data8> VALUES)
Parameters
Type Name Description
IExpression<Data8> NO Reference ID for the mailbox. Maximum number of mailboxes is 30
IExpression<Data8> BOXNAME Zero terminated string with the mailbox name
IExpression<Data8> TYPES Data type of the content of the mailbox
IExpression<Data8> FIFOSIZE Not used
IExpression<Data8> VALUES Number of values of the type (specified by TYPE).
Returns
Type Description
Opcode
Remarks
If data type DATA_S is selected then it requires that a zero terminated string is sent. Maximum mailbox size is 250 bytes. I.e. if type is string (DATA_S) then there can only be 1 string of maximum 250 bytes (incl. zero termination), or if array (DATA_A), then array size cannot be larger than 250 bytes. Dispatch status can return FAILBREAK
